						<summary>

						<p>This is undated and a little damaged. It refers itself to the reign of the Vaidumba king <hi rend="bold">Gaṇḍatriṇētra</hi> and states that when Mahārāja and <hi rend="bold">Bāṇarasa</hi> attacked <hi rend="bold">Sōramaḍi</hi> fort, <hi rend="bold">Noḻambi, Daḍiga, Rāchamalla</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Mayindaḍi</hi> who fought against them were overthrown and that a hero died in the battle. Evidently this refers to the same event as the one mentioned in the preceding inscription.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
